article.description: In a duel of desperation, the Golden State Warriors were determined, while the Memphis Grizzlies were demoralized.
article.headline: Jamison's 37 points enough to keep Grizzlies winless
article.linkText: Grizzlies rally, but fall to Warriors to stay winless
article.story:
MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Still seeking their first victory of the season, the Memphis Grizzlies waited too long to make a big run.
Jamison

Antawn Jamison had 37 points and 11 rebounds as the Golden State Warriors beat the winless Grizzlies 108-101 Monday night. ''We made several mistakes on defense. It cost us 10 points,'' Memphis coach Sidney Lowe said. ''We missed a lot of open shots.'' Despite the victory, Jamison wasn't happy that his team nearly blew a 100-82 lead with just more than 3 minutes left. ''It's something we've really got to work on,'' he said. ''We did such a phenomenal job of having an 18-point lead in the fourth quarter. That's unheard of unless you're the Lakers or someone like that.'' After struggling most of the game, Memphis (0-8) began to put on some pressure late in the fourth quarter -- after some of their fans had already started filing out. The game drew an announced crowd of 10,112, the lowest since the Grizzlies moved to Memphis from Vancouver last season. Lorenzen Wright hit a short jumper with 3:08 to play to trim the lead to 100-84 and begin a 10-point run for the Grizzlies. Memphis cut it to 104-101 on Jason Williams' layup with 21 seconds left. But Dean Oliver made two free throws to put Golden State up five, and Troy Murphy hit two more to seal it. Gilbert Arenas said the victory might be a turning point for the Warriors, who had lost six in a row. ''We can only go up from here,'' Arenas said. ''The team has to fight to win. We knew it was going to come down to the wire. We were two teams hungry to win.'' Erick Dampier had 18 points and 16 rebounds for Golden State, while Murphy added 18 points. The Grizzlies, the only team in the NBA without a victory, were led by Pau Gasol's 24 points. Gordan Giricek had 21, Wright added 18 and Wesley Person 15. The Warriors had 53 rebounds to 36 for the Grizzlies. Golden State started the fourth period with a 12-point run to take a 94-69 lead on short jumper by Adonal Foyle. The Warriors scored on 11 straight possession in the third period, going up 74-61 on a short jumper by Jiri Welsch with 2:14 to go. The Warriors went ahead by 13 points twice in the third after leading 48-45 at halftime. The Warriors dominated the boards in the first half, with a 21-4 advantage in the first period. Of those Golden State rebounds in the first quarter, 11 were offensive. The Grizzlies had one offensive rebound in the period. Game notes
The Grizzlies were without Stromile Swift, who missed the game for ''personal reasons'' involving his family, and Michael Dickerson, who is still struggling with back and groin injuries and is on the injured list. Dickerson missed all but four games last season with a stress fracture near the groin. ... Lowe said Dickerson was undergoing physical therapy, but when he will return was unknown. ''It's a serious routine and he really works at it,'' Lowe said. ... The Grizzlies' Brevin Knight was out with a sprained ankle. ... Golden State won the season series 3-1 last season. The Warriors are 19-9 all-time against the Grizzlies.
